{"name": "reldplayer", "metadata": {"name": "reldplayer", "version": "0.9.1", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["click", "pygetwindow", "pyldplayer"], "summary": "a superset to pyldplayer", "upload_time": 1732434660}, "documentation": ["# reldplayer\na superset to [pyldplayer](https://github.com/ZackaryW/pyldplayer)\n\n## Install\n```bash\npip install reldplayer\n```\nto install an older version:\n```bash\npip install reldplayer==0.2.1\n```\n\n## Features\n1. Provides additional overloading to obtain LDPlayer path\n2. `LDWindowMgr` and `LDWindow` helpes to quickly associate a window to a LDPlayer instance\n3. a cli tool to quickly interact with LDPlayer\n\n## CLI Usage\n```bash\nreldplay -q \"[1,2,3]\"           # to select 3 instances in id\nreldplay --name \"test\"          # to select instance named \"test\"\nreldplay --name \"test*\"         # to select instance with pattern \"test*\"\n```\nfor full list of commands, run `reldplay` without any arguments\n"], "modules": [{"name": "reldplayer.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "reldplayer.utils.activate_wnd", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "wnd", "type": {"name": "gw.Win32Window", "xref": {"fqname": "pygetwindow.Win32Window", "project": "pygetwindow"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Activates the given window if it is not already active.\n\nArgs:\n    wnd (gw.Window): The window to activate.\n\nReturns:\n    None\n\nRaises:\n    None"]}, {"name": "reldplayer.utils.get_screen_dimensions", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "monitor_index", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns the dimensions and position of a specific monitor.\n\nArgs:\n    monitor_index (int, optional): The index of the monitor to retrieve information from. Defaults to 0.\n\nReturns:\n    tuple: A tuple containing the width, height, x-coordinate, and y-coordinate of the monitor.\n\nRaises:\n    ValueError: If the monitor_index is invalid."]}, {"name": "reldplayer.utils.grid_orientation", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "wnds", "type": {"name": "typing.List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "gw.Win32Window", "xref": {"fqname": "pygetwindow.Win32Window", "project": "pygetwindow"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "row", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "col", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "maxwidth", "type": {"name": "float | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "maxheight", "type": {"name": "float | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "minwidth", "type": {"name": "float | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "minheight", "type": {"name": "float | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "monitor", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "sleepTime", "type": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Arrange the given windows in a grid layout with the specified number of rows and columns.\n\nArgs:\n    wnds (List[gw.Window]): The list of windows to arrange.\n    row (int): The number of rows in the grid layout.\n    col (int): The number of columns in the grid layout.\n    maxwidth (float, optional): The maximum width of each window. Defaults to None.\n    maxheight (float, optional): The maximum height of each window. Defaults to None.\n    minwidth (float, optional): The minimum width of each window. Defaults to None.\n    minheight (float, optional): The minimum height of each window. Defaults to None.\n    monitor (int, optional): The index of the monitor to use for the grid layout. Defaults to 0.\n    sleepTime (float, optional): The time to sleep between each window arrangement. Defaults to 0.2.\n\nReturns:\n    None\n\nRaises:\n    None"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "reldplayer", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "reldplayer.LDWindow", "xref": {"fqname": "reldplayer.ext.window.LDWindow", "project": null}}, {"name": "reldplayer.LDWindowCollection", "xref": {"fqname": "reldplayer.ext.windowCollection.LDWindowCollection", "project": null}}, {"name": "reldplayer.LDWindowMgr", "xref": {"fqname": "reldplayer.ext.windowMgr.LDWindowMgr", "project": null}}, {"name": "reldplayer.undone_overloads", "xref": {"fqname": "reldplayer.overloads.undone_overloads", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "reldplayer._internal.wndCtrl", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "reldplayer._internal.wndCtrl.pg", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "reldplayer._internal.wndCtrl.WndCtrlCom", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "reldplayer._internal.wndCtrl.WndCtrlCom._focus", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "reldplayer._internal.wndCtrl.WndCtrlCom.__methods", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "reldplayer._internal.wndCtrl.WndCtrlCom.__getattribute__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "name", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "reldplayer._internal.wndCtrl.WndCtrlCom.vo